Ahead of the reconvening of the Supreme Court on the governorship tussle  in Imo State, the Imo State Elders Council yesterday called on them to uphold Senator Hope Uzodinma as the governor of Imo State. The elders led by the acting chairman, Chief Sunday John Enyogasi (Okey 2000); former Minister, Dr Walter Ofonagoro; Senator Boniface Chukwudi; Prince Lemmy Akakem; and Chief Ezechi Chukwu made the disclosure at a briefing in Owerri, the Imo State capital. According to them, the council commends the verdict of the apex court on Imo, saying that Senator Uzodinma is capable of governing the state. They called on protesters in the state to desist and allow peace to reign in the state. Furthermore, Chief Enyogasi called on Imo people to rally round Governor Uzodinma saying “the Elders Council calls on all patriotic Imolites to rally round our divinely ordained Governor, Senator Uzodinma to move our dear state forward on the promised cardinal principles of prosperity, accountability, rule of law, infrastructural development and national connectivity”. The Elders Council strongly affirmed Senator Uzodinma as the man who Imo people freely voted for as the governor, adding that the people are happy with the verdict of the apex court. They commended the courage of the Supreme Court judges for “Standing up against all forms of intimidation and arm twisting from unpatriotic elements, and restored the hope of Imo electorate”. The briefing was attended by elder statesmen including former Director General of the Nigeria Sports Council, Dr Pat Ekeji amongst others.  